ted; it was the expected baseline. That quiet, immense pressure became the engine for his entire life, fueling a drive that left little room for error.\n\n5.\nLast fall, on a dusty trail high up on Mount Tam, his daughter Maya pointed across the bay toward the city. \u201cIt looks so small from here, Dad.\u201d The Salesforce Tower, a building that dominated his weekdays, was just a pin on the horizon. Sharing a water bottle and looking at the view, he felt a quiet, profound contentment that no closed deal had ever given him. This, he realized, was the new bottom line. Not the view from a boardroom window, but this exact view, with her."
